args:
Having shrewdly opted to remain in the palace
after the Other's departure, Emile makes the
rounds in hopes of improving his stock with
the citizens. But when he pays thieves to stage
a robbery and then commands his own men to
drive them off, it's clear little has changed.
I heard Prince {player_name} is\non his way north to squash\nsome invaders.
As did I. I wonder if that means his battle\nwith Empress Zethia ended in victory?
In that case, the lad's gone and left us\ncompletely ungoverned AND unprotected!
Too true. Prince Leonidas has shown no\nsigns of leaving Valkaheim, and Princess\nChelle is holed up in Rovetelle.
Prince Valyx, too, has yet to returnâ€”and\nPrince Phares seems to have just up\nand disappeared.
Now hold on a tick... Wasn't there one\nother royal offspring?
Was there? Pretty sure we covered\neveryone already.
Indeed. Excluding Empress Zethia, the late\nKing Aurelius had only five heirs.
Huh... I guess you're right. Silly old me!
...That's a sample of what's been said\naround the capital lately, Your Highness.
Rrrgh! They don't even REMEMBER me?!\nThose ignorant, tasteless, pea-brained\nsheeple!

Why does my name not dance across their
lips entwined with words of praise and
glory?! 'Tis I who now sit upon the throne
once claimed by the Other!
To be fair, all you really did was sneak\nin after everyone else left...
What was that, you mewling cur?!
N-nothing Your Highness! A gust of wind!
Hmph. Right. I will prove my grandeur\nto you and ALL the rabble! Ho, you there!
Devise a scheme to coerce the masses\ninto accepting my undeniable majesty\nand authority.

Yes, you! Here, how about this: I shall
count to five, and if you spit out something
truly idiotic I'll hack off your head and
save us all further embarrassment. One...
W-wait! Okay, umm... Oh, I've got it!
The general populace is fearful of\ndisorder and unrest now that the\nOther is gone, yes?
If you were to tour the capital and sow\npeace and comfort, you would surely\nearn the people's approval.
Hmm... HMMM... Yes. I like it.

You misunderstand. While you were
busy wagging your tongue, I was all the
while devising a plan in my head of a
coincidentally similar ilk.

In fact, I would have shared it earlier had
you not been hogging all the air in the
room! Yes, the credit for this plan is
mine and mine alone. Brilliant, as ever!
All right, everyone! Prepare yourselves\nfor a trip to town!
Now listen: you're gonna hand over all\nyour valuables, or I'm gonna hand me\nblade to your face. We clear?
Y-yes! You can take whatever you want,\njust don't hurt me!

You address the sixth scion of this great
Kingdom of Alberia, the true genius of the
royal family, and a hero worthy of both
song and legendâ€”Prince Emile!
Fear not, my cowering citizen! All shall\nbe well now that I am on the scene!
And you lot! There is nothing more \ndepraved than stealing from a lowly\nbusiness owner barely scraping by!
Listen, ï¼‚prince.ï¼‚ I dunno who you think\nyou are, but if it's a scrap yer lookin' for,\nthen bring it on!
You scoundrels leave me no choice. I shall\nbring the hammer of justice down upon\nyou without mercy!
W-what? We'll be the ones fighting...?\nI mean, not that I'm all that surprised...
Obviously, you dolt! I can't go getting\ninjured, can I? Now, ATTAAACK!
You IMBECILE! I was supposed to land\nthe final blow!
Might've helped if you told us that\nbeforehand...
Is it not your duty to deliver glory to your\nprince?! You should have known the\nmoment the battle began! And as for YOU!

You claim to be professionals, and yet you
cannot follow simple instructions?! I told
you to make the knockout FLASHY! Really
put on a show!
S-sorry, we just...got a bit nervous, is all.
Ugh, just do it like we rehearsed! If you\ndon't, you'll not get a single speck of gold\nfrom me.
*sigh* It is SO difficult to find good help\nthese days. All right, everyone, let us\ncontinue on to the next shop!
Of course not! Word of my strength and\nexcellence must spread throughout the\nentire city, so our quota is ten shops a day!
Must I instruct you on how to walk,\nsoldier?!
N-no, Your Highness! I'm coming!\n...I should've picked literally any\nother sibling to serve...
